data.title: Quentin Tarantino
data.text:
Caricature of Quentin Tarantino

Quentin Jerome Tarantino was born March 27, 1963. He is an American film director, screenwriter, producer, and actor. His career began in the late 1980s, when he wrote and directed My Best Friend's Birthday. In the early 1990s, Quentin Tarantino began his career as an independent filmmaker with the release of Reservoir Dogs in 1992. Tarantino's films have garnered both critical and commercial success. He has received many industry awards.

His films have been characterized as satirical and an aestheticization of violence.
